New Records: Devon Conway scored 90+ runs from 58 balls, joining a select group in the World Cup; Finn Allen scored 42 off 16 balls; Mitchell Santner and Tim Southee each took 3 wickets
Key Match Events: Opening partnership of 56 runs between Devon Conway and Finn Allen; Australia's batting collapse with key dismissals of David Warner, Aaron Finch, Mitchell Marsh, Tim Stoinis, and Steve Smith; Phillips' standout catch to dismiss Stoinis and Steve Smith
Pre-Game Insights: New Zealand's first win against Australia since 2011; Aaron Finch's decision to send New Zealand in to bat; historical context of the 2021 final in Dubai
Post-Match Reflections: Devon Conway's emotional reaction and praise for Finn Allen; the victory as a pivotal moment for New Zealand's World Cup campaign; challenges ahead for both teams in the tournament
Miscellaneous Highlights: Match was sold out at the Sydney Cricket Ground; high interest and rivalry between the teams; historical significance of the venue
